headline: DOV Q1 Earnings Call: Margin Expansion Amid Revenue Uncertainty and Tariff Headwinds
summary: Manufacturing company Dover (NYSE:DOV) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales flat year on year at $1.87 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.05 per share was 3.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
